If that was the case, and if you don’t already have this setup, a workflow hack would be to have a `package.json` file in the root of your `/lubrizol-lfp` directory. That could be as simple as e.g.
```{
  "name": "lubrizol-lfp",
  "scripts": {
    "fetch:all": "hs fetch / design_mgr --portal=lubrizol --overwrite"
  }
}```
Assuming `@HubSpot/cms-cli` is installed globally (`npm install -g @HubSpot/cms-cli`), then you’d be able to `yarn fetch:all` from your lubrizol root dir.

There are other ways to set that up, like having the CLI install as a local dep to that directory.  I can help you set that up if interested.
